pageContext.claim: “She [Jacky Rosen] voted no on tax cuts, no on better health care, no on border security, and Jacky voted in favor of deadly sanctuary cities.”
pageContext.analysis: Rosen voted in the House for comprehensive immigration reform in 2013, which included significant upgrades to border security and manpower. Trump complains that she doesn't support his border wall or the Republican plans he supported to repeal and replace the Affordable Care Act. Those plans hardly qualify as "better health care," since the Congressional Budget Office estimated millions fewer people would be insured as a result over 10 years.
